From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 13:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] NixOS installer fixes

On NixOS, the Nix wrapper provides `pai` on PATH — the installer
must not inject shell aliases, show macOS-specific prompts, or
display incorrect launch instructions.

Changes:
- Guard shell alias injection with NIX_STORE env check
- Show `pai` instead of `source ~/.zshrc && pai` on NixOS
- Skip macOS menu bar app prompt on Linux
- Use platform-appropriate Pulse wording on Linux
- Skip launchd plist validation on Linux
- Skip shell alias validation on NixOS
- Wait 5 seconds before process.exit so user can read summary (non-NixOS only)
- Fix Electron GUI: extend auto-close from 3s to 30s so user can read summary
- Fix Electron GUI: show `pai` instead of `source ~/.zshrc && pai`

